TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

$a1 = random(1,5,1);
$b1 = random(6,10,1);
$coef3 = 2;
$coef2 = 3*($a1+$b1);
$coef1 = 6*$a1*$b1;
$coef0 = random(1,11,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Consider the function \( f(x) = -$coef3 x^3 + $coef2 x^2 - $coef1 x + $coef0 \). This function has two critical numbers \(A<B\):
$BR
\( A = \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $a1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
and  \( B = \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $b1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\(f''(A)=\) \{ans_rule()\}
$BR
\(f''(B)=\) \{ans_rule()\}
EOT

$ans = - 6*$coef3*$a1+2*$coef2;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));
$ans = - 6*$coef3*$b1+2*$coef2;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

BEGIN_TEXT
$BR
Thus \(f(x)\) has a local \{ans_rule()\} at \(A\) (type in MAX or MIN)
END_TEXT
$ans = "MIN";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));
BEGIN_TEXT
$BR
and a local \{ans_rule()\} at \(B\) (type in MAX or MIN).
END_TEXT
$ans = "MAX";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));

